				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Patch Info if you havent seen it yet...<a name="61752"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 8:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mostly as expected, and I'm looking forward to trying out some of this new stuff.
<br />

<br />
One bard-unrelated thing caught my attention:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">- Clerics Symbol and Aegolism spell lines no longer require reagents.*</span></blockquote> 
<br />
/boggle.  They just whittle away at the things that make this game an engaging, interesting, immersive and coherent world, don't they? /sigh
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">- Bard PBAoE spells will no longer damage targets that are moving, however any other spell effects from the PBAoE spell will still be applied to the targets as usual.*</span></blockquote>
<br />
Oh, and some crap about &quot;Bard PBAE spells&quot;, whatever those are.
