				<td colspan="2"><span>I've never gained experiance this way; I've always enjoyed grouping much more...
<br />

<br />
But there are significant problems with bards exping this way. It even affects other players:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The server side lag due to PBAE kiting *is* substantial and *does* affect other players. I happen to be the exact person who knows exactly what I'm talking about here because I am the person who 1) helped write the new pathing system, and 2) wrote the new collision system, and 3) have spent literally weeks running server profiling tools testing server loads and identifying what causes server lag. It just so happens that running a bunch of NPCs around in a circle is bad for CPU server loads, and does affect everyone else that happens to be on the same hardware. This is server lag, not video lag. The server doesn't care how many corpses are sitting around stationary. But when the server is asked to run path finder code on dozens of NPCs as they do full collision math as they run over the zone geometry, the server slows down and everyone in the zone &amp; other zones on the box is affected. As a player you generally only notice tell lag or NPC warping, but it does affect gameplay in many ways. Minimizing server lag is an ongoing task for me and the other programmers, and when stuff like this hits the radar as being a problem it's a priority for us to fix it.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The change was also known to happen before the patch even came. We knew a week beforehand:
<br />

<br />
http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=2002
<br />

<br />
The mere idea of a bard being able to kill a nearly unlimited amount of NPCs in a set time span isn't right anyway...</span></td>
