				<td colspan="2"><span>Do you think for a second that the top bards on every server did not area kite??  Come on you, answer with a straight face.  Do you believe that the best of the best never area kited??
<br />

<br />
Case closed.  
<br />

<br />
You may be an ok bard or even a good one...the best bards area kited or choose not to...but they certainly made the choice vs not being able to....Choosing not to meant raiding...not swarm kiting or chanting.  Lamers chant, and swarm....why..because you can not swarm anything over lv57 for christ sake.
<br />

<br />
You could area red mobs.
<br />

<br />
I am very comfortable with how I have played and know how to play this class.  I would think that the best bards are busy raiding, and when they feel like solo...it sure the h*ll is not swarm kiting, or even chant kiting...it was for the best return on invested time...ya area.  Make exceptions, but for the most part....every Bard that was ever a role model to me on AB...was a dam good area kiter as well in the past.  All of them.  Faced with 5 hours of play time they would raid Time, or GoD or where ever, faced with an hour to solo...they might choose area kites.  Swarming low blues...LOL not likely....get out more often...any Bard hack or not can swarm...EVERYBODY can swarm.  You never even get close to the mob if you swarm.  It is a bigger exploit then area.  ZERO risk vs REWARD.  Massive trains that lag as much as a 10 kite.  
<br />

<br />
I could care less if area kiting is dead or not.
<br />

<br />
So not all good bards area kited...granted.
<br />

<br />
Lots of area kite bards were idiot newbies yes....granted.
<br />

<br />
The extra-ordinary Bards ALL AREA KITED at some point in the game...and it was not cheating, or exploiting, or poor morals.  
<br />

<br />
New expansion, overpowered ability for new expansion, nerfed...that is the whole story, the rest is BS smokescreen crap.
<br />

<br />
Moose
